Senate Resolution 439
By: Senator Hodges of the 3rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life of the Honorable Sheila M. McNeill and dedicating a road in her memory;
2 and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Honorable Sheila M. McNeill has long been recognized by the citizens of
4 this state for the vital role that she played in leadership and her deep personal commitment
5 to the welfare of the citizens of Georgia and the nation; and
6 WHEREAS, she diligently and conscientiously devoted innumerable hours of her time,
7 talent, and energy for 58 years to the Navy League, the only civilian organization dedicated
8 to supporting the sea services of the United States of which includes providing support to the
9 United States Navy, United States Marine Corps, United States Coast Guard, and United
10 States Flag Merchant Marine; and
11 WHEREAS, she served as the Navy League's 42nd national president, national vice president
12 for legislative affairs, national director of the United States Naval Sea Cadet Corps, and a
13 member of the National Maritime Policy Committee; and
14 WHEREAS, Senator McNeill was devoted to the betterment of her community and state as
15 a Georgia Senator representing Senate District 3 from 2021 to 2023; and
